{"author":{"id":"837b2176f32c8aa0e6451c57f356a863ffced5924eb6264b6c4a7bb61a9eccd0"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1533104617,"nonce":"ulmqtGLh5G02vjYXtotXEMReYVE=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwOTQ2Mjg4NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2010#issuecomment-409462885"},"message":"\u003e  Isn't it similar to what was done by @blankenberg in https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/tree/master/data_managers/data_manager_manual?\n\nThey are similar, but both serve a different use case. The advantage of the manual data manager is that it has no limits.\nThe advantages of data_manager_select_index_by_path are:\n- Checks whether indexes exist on the fileystem to prevent typo's\n- fully unit tested\n- Is coupled with all the supported indexes in Galaxy. That means that when you add an index and when `watch_tool_data_dir: true` in `config/galaxy.yml` you do not need to restart Galaxy.\n\nBoth are complementary as far as I am concerned, they do not bite each other.","files":null}]}